  p The video went viral. So Nas double down on this strategy:
  p.list.list__top 1) Short viral videos
  p.list 2) Set to the tune of!{' '}
    span.italic Old Town Road
  p.list.list__bottom 3) Link the full song underneath
  p And the views started piled up:
  p By February short videos featuring Old Town Road were everywhere on Twitter. The problem was none of them included the words!{' '}
    span.italic Old Town Road.
  p This made searching the song difficult. People would type “I got the horses in the back” and find nothing. Nas clocked this and changed the song title on YouTube and SoundCloud. He also made a post on the Name That Song subreddit which displayed on Google. Problem solved:
