  p Inspired by!{' '}
    span.italic Old Town Road's
    |!{' '}success on Twitter it spread to TikTok.!{' '}
    span The “Yee Haw Challenge” swept the platform and in a matter of weeks!{' '}
    | the whole of TikTok was dressed up as cowboys:
  video(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/otr3.mp4" class="img__50" playsinline="playsinline" preload="auto" controls="controls")
  p This momentum carried!{' '}
    span.italic Old Town Road
    |!{' '}onto Billboard’s country music charts, where it was quickly removed for “not being a country song”.
  p Ironically, this was the best thing that could have possibly happened. Billboard's decision turned
    span.italic Old Town Road
    |!{' '}into a national talking point and two weeks later it was No. 1 on Billboard.
  p Nas started recording remixes with some of music's biggest stars.
  p Billboard has a rule whereby remix plays count towards the original song's chart placement. When one remix waned Nas released another, and!{' '}
    span.italic Old Town Road
    |!{' '}, became impossible to budge.
  p Billboard has a rule whereby remix plays count towards the original song's chart placement.
  p Nas recorded remixes with Billy Rae Cyrus, Diplo, BTS, Young Thug and Mason Ramsey. When one remix waned another would came out, and it made!{' '}
    span.italic Old Town Road
    |!{' '}, impossible to displace.
  p 17 weeks later he'd broken Mariah Carey’s record for the most consecutive weeks at No. 1.
